I came across something interesting at [JoeGrossberg.com]({{% wayback "http://www.joegrossberg.com/archives/000683.html" %}}). I was using Internet Explorer temporarily while I tried to uninstall the latest [“nightly”]({{% wayback "http://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla/nightly/latest/" %}}) of [Mozilla]({{% wayback "http://www.mozilla.org" %}}), and re-install the last [Beta]({{% wayback "http://www.mozilla.org/releases/#1.4b" %}}) version.

If you’re using Internet Explorer:

```javascript
var oWMP = new ActiveXObject('WMPlayer.OCX.7');
var colCDROMS = oWMP.cdromCollection;
colCDROMS.Item(0).Eject();
```

Hmmm… can we all say “security violation”? Let’s see how long it takes Microsoft to fix this bug without an “MS Bugzilla”. On the other hand, with the [IE6]({{% wayback "http://news.com.com/2100-1032_3-1011859.html?tag=fd_top" %}}) [freeze]({{% wayback "http://www.web-graphics.com/mtarchive/000881.php" %}}), it may never get fixed…
